cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about evaluating different sequence-to-sequence models for word discovery, which is a task related to natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of metrics to evaluate the quality of soft-alignment matrices, which is related to machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes an improvement to the best model using an alignment entropy confidence measure, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper deals with low-resource scenarios, which is a common topic in neural machine translation and language modeling, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
